Two separate issues here:

**1. `StaticResource` doesn't update at runtime.**
`StaticResource` resolves once at XAML load time. Switch to `DynamicResource` so bindings re-evaluate when you swap the `ResourceDictionary`:

```xml
<!-- ✗ won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✓ updates on theme change -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes in code-behind:

```csharp
// In your theme toggle handler
var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDicts.Clear();
mergedDicts.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

**2. Android recreates the `Activity` on config changes.**
By default, toggling system dark mode triggers a configuration change that destroys and recreates your `Activity`. To handle it in-place, add `ConfigurationChanges` to your `MainActivity`:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.UiMode
        | ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
        | ConfigChanges.Orientation)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

Then detect the system change and apply your theme:

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs or a service
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    bool useDark = e.RequestedTheme == AppTheme.Dark;
    var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
    mergedDicts.Clear();
    mergedDicts.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
};
```

**TL;DR:** `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` for live updates; add `ConfigChanges.UiMode` to prevent activity restart on system theme toggle.
